In today's episode our guest is Dr. Vikas Divyakirti, Educator & Author. This episode explores power, politics, geopolitics, and the global shifts reshaping the 21st century.

We discuss geopolitics, society, and how India is evolving. Dr. Vikas Divyakirti talks about the cultural differences between Delhi and Mumbai, why Mumbai feels more open and professional, while Delhi has a stronger political tone. He explains why making a mistake and admitting it openly matters, especially in political spaces. We also discuss how India is moving between left and right ideologies, and how a convergence is slowly forming.

We also touch upon global power, leadership, and education. Russia and America have enough nuclear power to destroy the world many times over. Trumpâ€™s unapologetic, business-first approach reflects a different mindset of leadership. Dr. Vikas discusses how teacher salaries in India are far lower than in countries like the US and UK, affecting both quality and satisfaction in education. If youâ€™re curious about world affairs, political psychology, or Indiaâ€™s geopolitical standing, this is one of the most important conversations youâ€™ll hear.

In today's episode, our guest is Dr. Tarang Krishna, Cancer Healer, Coach and MD at the Cancer Healer Center. In this episode, he tells us what actually happens in the first 72 hours when cancer begins forming in the body, why small recurring irritations matter, and how early signs like diarrhoea, constipation or constant discomfort often get ignored. He explains why cancer develops only when immunity drops and why preventive testing, including CBC, LFT, CA-125, CEA, thyroid and liver profiles, is crucial for catching it early.

We also explore his S.M.I.L.E. formula for building immunity: prioritising sleep, keeping the body in movement, choosing immunity-boosting foods, staying surrounded by love, and getting daily sunlight. Dr Krishna discusses the dangers of everyday habits, such as consuming burnt food, using aluminium cookware, drinking from plastic bottles, and exposing ourselves to chemicals in nail polish, toothpaste, and shampoos. 

In the final part, he discusses how people can retrain their bodies after a cancer diagnosis through strong willpower, movement, meditation and emotional release. We talk about why young people today fall ill more often, the lessons from Blue Zones, the hidden toxins inside your pillow, the link between melatonin and cancer, and the role of spiritual health in healing.

At a recent meet-up demonstrating our AI-powered "Friendly Meals" app, someone asked the ultimate question: "Did you ever use this app to actually cook something?" We realized we hadn't... yet.

Join Peter, Marina, and Rosario in Google's kitchen as they put Firebase AI logic to the ultimate real-world test. Watch as they use the Friendly Meals app to snap photos of random ingredients in the fridge and let Gemini generate a recipe for a tasty Parmigiana on the fly. 

Friendly Meals demonstrates how Firebase AI logic can be used on Android, iOS, Flutter, and the web to provide secure access to Gemini, allowing you to create amazing AI experiences in your own apps.

title: FII and DII are buying these 3 stocks?
description:
Three fundamentally strong companies where Foreign Institutional Investors (FIIs) and Domestic Institutional Investors (DIIs) have significantly increased their holdings in recent quarters. This confidence is notable given that FIIs collectively withdrew approximately â‚¹1.98 lakh crore from the Indian market in 2025.

The first company, a major manufacturer of wires, cables, and Fast Moving Electrical Goods (FMEG), achieved an 18% YoY revenue growth and a 56% increase in Net Profit in Q2 FY26. Key financials are strong, though the script highlights risks associated with high inventory and receivables, which strain the adjusted Cash Flow from Operations (CFO).

The second company, focused on batteries and electronics for sectors like defense and railways, saw exceptional performance driven by specific rail orders, leading to a 135% YoY revenue jump and 345% growth in Net Profit. However, a major challenge is the deterioration of cash conversion, with the CFO/PAT ratio falling sharply to 28% in H1 FY26.

The third company operates as a Contract Research, Development & Manufacturing Organization (CRDMO) for global pharma firms. It reported a 100% rise in Profit After Tax (PAT) on 36% revenue growth. Despite aggressive investment plans and having cleared long-term debt, this company also faces tighter liquidity as its CFO/PAT ratio has dropped due to growing trade receivables.
The overall discussion emphasizes that while institutional buying signals confidence, thorough research into underlying fundamentals and cash flow is equally important.

title: Firebase After Hours #19: Data Connect, Kotlin & SQL: A New Firebase Stack
description:
As an Android developer, you've come to love the simplicity of Firebase. But what happens when your app's data model is truly relational and you find yourself needing the power of a SQL database?

On this Firebase After Hours, we're diving into Firebase Data Connect, with a special focus on what it means for you: the new type-safe Kotlin SDK.

Join us as we explore Data Connect from an Android developer's perspective. You'll see how it integrates with Firebase Auth and generates a native Kotlin SDK, making it easier than ever for you to build powerful, data-driven Android apps backed by Cloud SQL.


We'll cover:
* The "Why": Data Connect for the native Android developer.
* Live Demo: Building a Kotlin app with a PostgreSQL backend.
* Exploring the generated type-safe Kotlin code.
* Live Q&A for your Android and backend questions!

In today's episode, our guest is Dr. Vikas Divyakirti, Educator & Author. In this episode, we talk about how perception shapes our entire life. Dr. Vikas Divyakirti explains how people often see him as â€œtoo serious,â€ while in reality, heâ€™s fun, active in sports, and very different from the image created around him. He says society keeps telling us to be â€œidealâ€ , good at dance, sports, grooming, and understanding people but trying to be ideal only makes life harder. Itâ€™s much better to simply be a comfortable and real human being.

We also discuss self-esteem and how many of us feel shy to ask for help because of an unconscious fear of â€œkya chukaana padega?â€ Some people struggle to say no easily, and that can become a lifelong burden. Vikas talks about how being known publicly means even small issues get highlighted like when CCPA fined many institutions but the spotlight came only on him.

The episode then moves into relationships, evolution, and loneliness. How men and women choose partners is mostly driven by evolutionary psychology, not logic. Most relationships run on cost-benefit analysis, and marriage may reduce in the future. We talk about why people cheat because of the clash between our genes that push us to seek variety and a society that demands monogamy and â€œsanskaar.â€ The conversation ends with loneliness, modern emotional needs, and how humans today struggle between biology and expectations.

title: 3 Beaten down stocks with growing fundamentals?
description:
Why are some companies seeing double-digit profit growth while their stock prices plummet?

 This video dives deep into the financials of three high-growth stocks that have seen their share prices fall by more than 30% from their 52-week highs.

These businesses boast remarkable 3-year performance metrics, with Sales CAGR reaching up to 79% and Profit CAGR reaching up to 98%.

We analyze the reasons behind this disconnect:

1. The Infrastructure Play: A real estate company aggressively expanding into the high-growth data center and cloud services sector, projecting massive future revenue from this new diversification.

2. The Turnaround Story: An integrated wind energy solutions provider that recently flipped its financials from massive losses to strong profitability, driven by backward integration and strong execution in its core products.

3. The Renewables Specialist: A turnkey wind power developer leveraging a massive 2+ GW order book and increasing its annuity-based revenue, but managing risks like revenue concentration.
Is this price correction purely due to market sentiment, or are fundamental challengesâ€”such as aggressive valuations, working capital management, or execution delaysâ€”coming into play? Watch the full breakdown to determine which of these companies truly aligns growth and long-term value!

title: Implementing chat with Firebase AI Logic on iOS
description:
Learn how to build a powerful, AI-powered chat feature for your iOS app! In this video, https://www.youtube.com/@PeterFriese from the Firebase team shows you how to use Firebase AI Logic to create a conversational interface from scratch.

We'll start by tackling the biggest challenge in AI chat: the "stateless" nature of LLMs. You'll learn why models have no "memory" and how Firebase AI Logic's Chat API (sendMessage) automatically manages conversation history for you, making complex, multi-turn conversations possible.

Using a "Friendly Meals" sample app built with Swift and SwiftUI, you will learn how to:
Set up the Gemini 2.5 Flash model with Firebase.
Use System Instructions to give your AI a unique personality.
Enable multimodal chat (sending images like PNGs and JPEGs).
Implement real-time streaming responses (sendMessageStream) to create a smooth, modern UX and avoid lag.

01:58 - LLMs can't actually keep conversation history ğŸ¤¯

title: Home is where the heart is. Shreyanka Patil expresse her delight at being retained by RCB!
3 healthcare stocks rapidly expanding their business capacities?
description:
India's domestic healthcare industry is entering a massive growth phase, with the core healthcare delivery segment projected to reach â‚¹9.4â€“9.8 lakh crore by FY28. This rapid expansion is supported by factors like an aging population, rising lifestyle diseases, and medical tourism, which is expected to reach USD 58.2 billion by 2035.

This video features three prominent hospital chains that are leveraging this market momentum by planning to double their existing bed capacities.

The first company, a major player primarily located in Tier 1 cities, reports the industryâ€™s highest occupancy rate (76% in Q1 FY26). They are funding their substantial capacity addition largely through internal accruals, aiming for a zero-debt approach to expansion. A second major multi-speciality provider, focused on North and East India, is driving growth through significant greenfield (new hospital) additions, reporting robust Q1 FY26 net profit growth of nearly 50%. Lastly, a Western India focused provider also targets doubling its bed count, supporting its growth strategy with a mix of internal cash and debt.

While all three show strong revenue and profitability gains (driven by higher capacity utilisation and improved Average Revenue Per Occupied Bed), high market valuations across the sector suggest that investors must carefully assess how these ambitious expansion plans will translate into sustainable future profits.

title: 3 strongest mid-cap breakout stocks after long consolidation
description:
This video delves into three best momentum breakout stocks selected from the Nifty Midcap 100 index, following the index's own breakout after consolidating for more than a year. 

The analysis focuses on determining whether the recent technical spikes are short-term anomalies or the start of genuine re-ratings based on momentum and fundamental strength.

We analyze companies across three distinct sectors: Renewable Energy Manufacturing, Oil Marketing/Refining, and Industrial Power Generation.

One company in the renewable sector has seen explosive three-year profit growth (191% CAGR), fueled by high import duties, government capacity allocations, and strategic acquisitions, leading to a massive expansion of operating margins (4% to 19%). Its future is supported by a large order book of around â‚¹47,000 crores.

A second major energy player, which just broke out after 1.5 years of consolidation, showed a remarkable earnings rebound in H1 FY26 (Net Profit expanded 10x) due to improved cost management and record Gross Marketing Margins.

The third company, a manufacturer of engines, hit a new all-time high after tight consolidation, benefiting from secular tailwinds like the domestic power generation segment's robust growth, particularly demand from the burgeoning data center industry.

The video also discusses key risks for these companies, such as export uncertainties and US anti-dumping probes for the first company, and the inherent cyclicality and domestic under-recovery pressures affecting the energy marketer.
